## Key Features

### Independent Services
- Frontend and backend can be developed, tested, and deployed independently
- Clear API contracts via OpenAPI/Swagger documentation
- Shared JSON schemas ensure data consistency

### KRaft-Mode Kafka
- Modern Kafka setup without Zookeeper dependency
- Simplified cluster management
- Built-in health checks and monitoring

### Sandboxed Enrichment
- User-defined Python scripts for message transformation
- Secure subprocess execution with timeout protection
- Error capture and reporting

### Production-Ready
- Docker containerization for all components
- Environment-based configuration
- Health checks and monitoring endpoints
- CORS configuration for frontend integration

### Developer-Friendly
- Hot-reloading for both frontend and backend
- Interactive API documentation (Swagger UI)
- Comprehensive README files for each component
- Example scripts and configurations

## Quick Start Commands

### Start Infrastructure
```bash
cd infra
docker-compose up -d
```

### Start Frontend
```bash
cd frontend
npm install
cp .env.example .env.local
npm start
```

### Access Services
- Frontend: http://localhost:4200
- Backend API: http://localhost:8000/docs
- Kafka UI: http://localhost:8080
- Schema Registry: http://localhost:8081

